SIMPLE: retract
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retract
<hw>Re*tract"</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*tr⟦amac⟧kt")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Retracted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Retracting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧tracter</ets>, L. <ets>retractare</ets>,
<ets>retractatum</ets>, to handle again, reconsider, retract, fr.
<ets>retrahere</ets>, <ets>retractum</ets>, to draw back. See
<er>Retreat</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To draw back; to draw up or
shorten; <as>as, the cat can <ex>retract</ex> its claws; to
<ex>retract</ex> a muscle.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To withdraw; to recall; to disavow; to recant; to
take back; <as>as, to <ex>retract</ex> an accusation or an
assertion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would as freely have <qex>retracted</qex> this charge of
idolatry as I ever made it.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To take back,, as a grant or favor previously
bestowed; to revoke.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To recall; withdraw; rescind; revoke; unsay;
disavow; recant; abjure; disown.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retract</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Retract
<hw>Re*tract"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To draw back; to
draw up; <as>as, muscles <ex>retract</ex> after
amputation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take back what has been said; to withdraw a
concession or a declaration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She will, and she will not; she grants, denies,⟦br⟧
Consents, <qex>retracts</qex>, advances, and then files.</q>
<rj><qau>Granville.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retract</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Retract
<hw>Re*tract"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>The pricking of
a horse's foot in nailing on a shoe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retractable</ent>⟦br⟧
